meta {
  name: Tool Calls Per Day Breach
  type: http
  seq: 3
}

post {
  url: {{base_url}}/chat
  body: json
  auth: bearer
}

auth:bearer {
  token: {{auth_token}}
}

body:json {
  {
    "message": "find me a good coffee shop"
  }
}

docs {
  ## Precondition
  User's `toolCalls.count` must be at or above the plan threshold (30 for homebody).
  Accumulate via done responses from prior successful chat calls where FastAPI returns
  `tool_calls_used > 0`. Sessions and turns must be below their limits.

  ## Expected Response
  HTTP 429 — Too Many Requests

  ```json
  {
    "error": "rate_limit_exceeded",
    "limit": "tool_calls_per_day",
    "limit_value": 30
  }
  ```

  ## Notes
  - tool_calls is checked FIRST in the guard (before turns and sessions)
  - Counters update in ChatService after each successful response from FastAPI
  - Counter resets at UTC midnight — `new Date().toISOString().slice(0,10)` is the boundary
  - NestJS server must be running on port 3333: `pnpm nx serve api`
}
